segment.source: To obtain the font, you must install Windows 10.
segment.target: To obtain the font, you must install Windows 10.

segment.source: Use these glyphs only when you can explicitly specify the Segoe MDL2 Assets font.

segment.source: The Windows 8/8.1 Segoe UI Symbol icon font has been replaced with the Segoe MDL2 Assets font effective with the release of Windows 10.
segment.target: The Windows 8/8.1 Segoe UI Symbol icon font has been replaced with the Segoe MDL2 Assets font effective with the release of Windows 10.

segment.source: It can be used in much the same manner as the older font, but many glyphs have been redrawn in the Windows 10 icon style with the font’s metrics set so that icons are aligned within the font’s em-square instead of on a typographic baseline.
segment.target: It can be used in much the same manner as the older font, but many glyphs have been redrawn in the Windows 10 icon style with the font’s metrics set so that icons are aligned within the font’s em-square instead of on a typographic baseline.

segment.source: Note An Em is a unit of measure in the font.
segment.target: Note An Em is a unit of measure in the font.

segment.source: 1 Em in the font is equal to 100% of the specified point value at 72ppi.
segment.target: 1 Em in the font is equal to 100% of the specified point value at 72ppi.

segment.source: For example 16pt is equal to 16px at 72ppi (aka 100% Plateau).
segment.target: For example 16pt is equal to 16px at 72ppi (aka 100% Plateau).

segment.source: The new MDL2 fonts are designed so that the footprint of the icon area is a square Em.
segment.target: The new MDL2 fonts are designed so that the footprint of the icon area is a square Em.

segment.source: So if you put 16px for Width and Height in the code, you get a 16x16px icon footprint.
segment.target: So if you put 16px for Width and Height in the code, you get a 16x16px icon footprint.

segment.source: That does not always mean the icon will be the full dimension of the footprint.
segment.target: That does not always mean the icon will be the full dimension of the footprint.

segment.source: The Segoe UI Symbol will still be available as a "legacy" resource.
segment.target: The Segoe UI Symbol will still be available as a "legacy" resource.

segment.source: But it is advised that all applications be updated to use the new Segoe MDL2 Assets.
segment.target: But it is advised that all applications be updated to use the new Segoe MDL2 Assets.

segment.source: Most of the icons and UI controls included in the Segoe MDL2 Assets font are mapped to the Private Use Area of Unicode (PUA).
segment.target: Most of the icons and UI controls included in the Segoe MDL2 Assets font are mapped to the Private Use Area of Unicode (PUA).

segment.source: The PUA allows font developers to assign private Unicode values to glyphs that don’t map to existing code points.
segment.target: The PUA allows font developers to assign private Unicode values to glyphs that don’t map to existing code points.

segment.source: This is useful when creating a symbol font, but it creates an interoperability problem.

segment.source: Unlike with Segoe UI Symbol, the icons in the Segoe MDL2 Assets font are not intended for use in-line with text.
segment.target: Unlike with Segoe UI Symbol, the icons in the Segoe MDL2 Assets font are not intended for use in-line with text.

segment.source: This means that some older "tricks" like the progressive disclosure arrows no longer apply.

segment.source: Likewise, since all of the new icons are sized and positioned the same, they do not have to be made with zero width; we have just made sure they work as a set.

segment.source: Segoe UI Symbol also relied on “zero width” glyphs for layering and colorization, as in this example, a black outline (U+E006) could be drawn on top of the zero-width red heart (U+E00B).
segment.target: Segoe UI Symbol also relied on “zero width” glyphs for layering and colorization, as in this example, a black outline (U+E006) could be drawn on top of the zero-width red heart (U+E00B).

segment.source: All glyphs in Segoe MDL2 Assets have the same fixed width with a consistent height and left origin point, so layering and colorization effects can be achieved by drawing glyphs directly on top of each other.
